FBIS4-14141 "drnes082_r_94009" FBIS-NES-94-082 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 India Government Approves German, U.S. Joint Ventures Government Approves German, U.S. Joint Ventures BK2804050594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 28 Apr 94 BK2804050594 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The government has approved setting up of a joint venture company with Germany in the field of engineering. It will have collaboration between the Mettalurgical and Engineering Consultants India Limited, MECON, and LPOAG [expansion unknown] of Germany. The new company will have an initial paid-up capital of 40 lakh rupees with the German company contributing 74 percent. The company will deal with designing and manufacturing of electrical, electronic automation, and electro mechanical equipment for industrial plants. The union cabinet also approved another joint venture company by MECON with a U.S. computer software company. It will harness information technology for mettalurgical, chemical, and refining industries. It will have equity of two and a half crore rupees.
